THRESHOLD
  Set the minimum stockpile level maintained by distribution.

SYNTAX
  threshold <commodity> [<sects>] [<amount>]
  thre      <commodity> [<sects>] [<amount>]

DESCRIPTION
  Sets the threshold for a commodity in a sector.  During each
  update, the distribution system moves commodities so that each
  sector maintains at least its threshold amount.

  If <amount> is omitted, displays current thresholds.
  If <amount> is 0, clears the threshold.

  A sector will import from its distribution center if below
  threshold, and export the surplus above threshold to the center.

  <sects> accepts the full sector spec syntax including realm numbers
  (#N) and designation conditions (?des=X).  The ?des=X condition must
  be attached directly to the spec with no space.

  Commodity mnemonics:
    c=civ  m=mil  u=uw  f=food  s=shell  g=gun  p=petrol
    i=iron  d=dust  b=bar  o=oil  l=lcm  h=hcm  r=rad

EXAMPLE
  threshold food * 30            keep 30 food in every sector
  threshold food 0,0 2000        keep 2000 food in capital
  threshold iron -4,2 50         mine keeps 50 iron
  threshold dust *               show all dust thresholds
  threshold food #1 100          keep 100 food in every realm 1 sector
  threshold iron #1?des=m 200    keep 200 iron in realm 1 iron mines
  threshold lcm *?des=k 500      keep 500 lcm in all lcm factories
  threshold food *?des=a 50      keep 50 food in all agribusiness

